  "description": "Torus T(4,3) — a perfect fourth (4:3 ratio). Combined with high entrainment (0.6) and max spread (0.9), this creates a choir of 6 voices spread across the stereo field, all locked into fourth-based harmony. The meridian of the torus divides the delay matrix into two symmetric halves like a choir split into sections.",
